I've played many mobile games over the years and, although I enjoyed many, I wasn't challenged by any... until Project Highrise. The only difficulty I encounter with other games is trying to enjoy free games for free. This game isn't free and doesn't claim to be, but it is definitely well-worth it's small, one-time cost. I was shocked by how detailed and realistically complex the game play is. I started with the tutorials and then went on to the normal-level (difficulty) sandbox mode. I expected to easily progress, but that's not what happened lol. In fact, I had to start over 6 TIMES before I finally was able to stabilize my Highrise with a daily profit. Please understand, I'm not trying to discourage anyone. In fact, I suggest everyone get this game! Project Highrise is the only game (so far) that provides a real challenge for veteran mobile gamers. I was up until 3 am last night and the time flew by! I can't stress it enough... YOU NEED TO TRY THIS GAME! If I had to make a suggestion on ways to improve/enhance, it would be the ability to further customize the aesthetics via color and/or more style alterations. However, even without that ability, this is still a 5 star experience!

I guess you will pick the highest value one anyway. Should have stayed the old sim tower way to play. Let me zone the building and set the price and tenants will come if my building is attractive, or abandoned it otherwise. I had restaurants in my building losing money from day 1 but they seems to happily staying there to pay rent for a very very long time, until I kick it out. They only leave if you do stupid thing (e.g. cut their power). Weird. Don't want to pay the penalty to kick someone out? Just cut their power! They will leave for free! LOL. Lifts are basically teleports. There is nothing to manage. One big disappointment if you were coming from Sim Tower. Power, water, gas... systems are unnecessary in this game. They are irritating and doesn't add value to the game. Spend your efforts to develop more interesting stuff. Good luck.

I love love love this game. Like, its the only mobile game I've put serious 
time into. But it has a game breaking bug that has completely soured my 
experience. I accidently placed the outdoors tree in my 50+story highrise, 
not knowing that not only would they glitch through the floor, they would 
keep you from building on the next level because the tree doesn't allow 
building above it, effectively capping my progress right there as you can 
only build where there is a foundation. This is a bug because the trees 
cannot be bulldozed due to parkland rules, even though it's inside my 
building. Please fix this.
replyContent:
We are sorry to hear that you have an issue. Please contact our support, so we can identify the issue and help you. 

Your issue has been fixed with the latest update.
